==English==

===Etymology===
From middle english [[artillerie]], from old french [[artillerie]].

===Noun===
'''artillery'''

# Large cannon like weapons, transportable and usually operated by more than one person
# A unit of the army, that uses such weapons
# [[gunnery]]

